                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/15.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Legation at Peking today telegraphs as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The Chinese Government appreciates friendly offices of the United States
                            Government and request further representations to Panama. Objection is
                            made to Articles 7, 14 and 25 of registration regulations making
                            excessive charges for registration, requiring Chinese to report every
                            six months and placing enormous tax upon societies. The principal
                            objection is to reporting every six months.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
